properties.name: Outback Steakhouse 972-516-4100
properties.description: Posted by Terrys 1569 N. Central ExpresswayGood ribeye and sirloin steaks, crispy outside, warm and bloody inside (medium rare); the rare have a cold middle. Seasoning is salty, so ask them to leave it off. Good prime rib. Baked potatoes are covered in coarse salt, but they\'ll rinse them for you. Salad dressings are salty, but they do have an OK wine vinegar and a totally bland olive oil - probably best to take your own dressing. The Blooming Onion has awesome flavor, but enough salt to satisfy a herd of goats for a year. Avoid it. The cheesecake is pedestrian at best, and tastes very refrigerated, if you know what I mean. Most other desserts sampled are icky sweet. Hours: MON-THU 4:00 pm-10:30 pm FRI 4:00 pm-11:00 pm SAT 3:00 pm-11:00 pm SUN 3:00 pm-10:30 pm
